<BaseLayout title="Consultancy — grimbergIT">
  <article class="surface">
    <p class="eyebrow">Engagements</p>
    <h1>Consultancy</h1>
    <p>
      I help engineering teams get unstuck: platform choices, reliability, delivery flow, and the
      slow work of making complex systems legible again.
    </p>

    <h2>Where I add value</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Kubernetes / platform architecture — pragmatic, not cargo-cult.</li>
      <li>Incident response and post-incident learning.</li>
      <li>Developer experience: build pipelines, test strategy, on-call sanity.</li>
      <li>Migrating monoliths without pretending they're the enemy.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How I work</h2>
    <p>
      Short engagements (2–6 weeks). I embed with the team, write down what I learn, and leave a
      trail others can follow after I'm gone. No slide decks unless you ask.
    </p>

    <p><a href="/contact">Get in touch →</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
